      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implement asynchronous calls to handle high loads, and monitor memory usage to prevent bottlenecks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "API Integration and Configuration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrate Ben2 endpoints into your application stack. Use RESTful APIs for simplicity or gRPC for low-latency communication. Example curl command for inference: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "curl -X POST https://api.ben2.com/v1/ben2q/infer -H 'Authorization: Bearer <token>' -d '{\"input\": \"data\"}'",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Ensure error handling for rate limits and retries with exponential backoff."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Troubleshooting and Maintenance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common issues include connection timeouts and model drift. Implement logging with structured formats (e.g., JSON) for easy parsing. Set up alerts for API error rates above 1% and regularly update the Ben2 client to incorporate bug fixes. Use the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/v1/ben2q/status",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint to monitor model health and perform rolling updates without downtime."
          }
        ]
